    {
      "name": "4. Token Usage Tracking",
      "description": "Track and manage monthly token usage for rate limiting",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Token Usage (via Chat Endpoint)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// The chat endpoint returns token usage in response headers",
                  "// and in the response body",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Check for rate limit headers",
                  "var rateLimitHeader = pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Remaining');",
                  "if (rateLimitHeader) {",
                  "    console.log('Rate Limit Remaining:', rateLimitHeader);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (jsonData.token_usage) {",
                  "    console.log('Token Usage:', JSON.stringify(jsonData.token_usage));",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"message\": \"Hello, what is your investment philosophy?\",\n    \"session_id\": \"postman-test-session\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/chat",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["chat"]
            },
            "description": "Send a chat message and observe token usage in the response.\n\nThe response includes:\n- `token_usage.input_tokens`: Tokens used for input\n- `token_usage.output_tokens`: Tokens used for output\n- `token_usage.total_tokens`: Total tokens consumed\n- `token_usage.token_limit`: Monthly limit\n- `token_usage.percent_used`: Percentage of limit used\n- `token_usage.remaining_tokens`: Tokens remaining this month"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Check Token Usage in Follow-up Response",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// The follow-up endpoint returns token usage in the 'complete' event",
                  "// Look for the last SSE event in the response",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Parse SSE response to find token_usage",
                  "var body = pm.response.text();",
                  "var completeMatch = body.match(/event:\\s*complete[\\s\\S]*?data:\\s*({[^\\n]+})/);",
                  "if (completeMatch) {",
                  "    try {",
                  "        var completeData = JSON.parse(completeMatch[1]);",
                  "        if (completeData.token_usage) {",
                  "            console.log('Token Usage:', JSON.stringify(completeData.token_usage, null, 2));",
                  "            console.log('Input tokens:', completeData.token_usage.input_tokens);",
                  "            console.log('Output tokens:', completeData.token_usage.output_tokens);",
                  "            console.log('Percent used:', completeData.token_usage.percent_used + '%');",
                  "        }",
                  "    } catch (e) {",
                  "        console.log('Could not parse complete event');",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "text/event-stream"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"question\": \"Give me a quick summary of the executive summary\",\n    \"session_id\": \"{{session_id}}\",\n    \"ticker\": \"{{ticker}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/research/followup",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["research", "followup"]
            },
            "description": "The follow-up endpoint returns token usage in the final 'complete' SSE event.\n\n**Token usage fields in response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"token_usage\": {\n    \"input_tokens\": 150,\n    \"output_tokens\": 450,\n    \"total_tokens\": 600,\n    \"token_limit\": 500000,\n    \"percent_used\": 0.12,\n    \"remaining_tokens\": 499400,\n    \"threshold_reached\": null\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Threshold notifications:**\n- `threshold_reached`: null (under 80%), \"80\" (80-89%), \"90\" (90-99%), \"100\" (limit reached)"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
